				<wikidot:authorName>towwl</wikidot:authorName>				<wikidot:authorUserId>3153718</wikidot:authorUserId>				<content:encoded>
					<![CDATA[
						 <p><span style="text-decoration: line-through;">Maybe it's because I haven't looked at 4800 yet, but I don't understand why 4799 is Keter. Maybe some of what the captured member says in the interviews is scary and possibly world ending, but the smuggling crew itself isn't responsible for any possible apocalyptic scenario. There isn't any indication that they have hostile intentions beyond protecting one another, or even that they're interested in coming back.</span></p> <p>EDIT: bah, pardon me. I blanked on the reason these things are Keter in the first place.</p> 
				 	]]>
				</content:encoded>							</item>
